Create after Step 12 and before writing strong teleconnection prose. It should:

derive annual detrended anomalies of wind, pressure, and corrected precipitation from Step 08 annual outputs;
correlate them with the same indices/lags using the same valid-year logic as Step 10;
output lake-level associations and regional summaries;
allow a three-link descriptive test:

index → local forcing anomaly
local forcing anomaly → LSWT anomaly
index → LSWT anomaly
Call this a pathway-consistency or mediation hypothesis, not formal causal mediation unless all temporal/confounding assumptions are explicitly modelled.




